<HEADLINE> Dinamo Bucharest Sacks Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Dinamo Bucharest, knocked out of
the UEFA Cup by a team of Icelandic amateurs, dismissed their
coach on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dinamo fell to KR Reykjavik, winners in both the home
and away matches, with an astonishing 4-1 aggregate against the
Romanian side.
</P>
<P>
Club officials moved swiftly to sack coach Cornel Talnar.
His duties were assumed by Viorel Hizo, Dinamo's coach in
1995 before moving on to Rapid Bucharest, the Romanian capital's
third club. 
</P>
</TEXT>
