<HEADLINE> EU Calls for Free Elections in Serbia and Montenegro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) today
called for a free and democratic election in Serbia and
Montenegro, a statement issued by the union's Luxembourg
presidency said.
</P>
<P>
It urged authorities of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia to
keep to their commitments, to accept outside observations during and
before the elections scheduled for September 21.
</P>
<P>
The statement requested all political forces of the federal
republic and new federal president, Slobodan Milosevic, to clearly
show willingness to take up the political and economic challenges
and to assume their responsibility.
</P>
<P>
The international community, the statement said, is ready to
help the country to recover its economy but expects it to
cooperate to create favorable conditions for the help. 
</P>
