<HEADLINE> Soeharto Calls for Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto
today urged the international community to seek ways to implement
development and improve their welfare without causing damage to
the environment.
</P>
<P>
Opening the third international conference on zero emissions
held here at the State Palace, the president stressed that the
world is in danger as a result of the destruction of the
environment and ecosystem.
</P>
<P>
"The Earth Summit in Rio de Janeiro has encouraged an economic
development that is friendly to the environment, namely
sustainable development through activities that consider both
environmental and development aspects," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he noted, the environment has been further
deteriorated five years after the Earth Summit and the developed
countries were obligated to deal with water and air pollution,
acid rains and an increasing volume of dangerous and poisonous
wastes.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot imagine the sufferings that will befall our children
and grandchildren if we ignore the threat to the environment,"
Soeharto said.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the three-day conference is the symbiosis between
global environment and industrial growth.  
</P>
</TEXT>
