<HEADLINE> Syrian President Arrives in Iran for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez Al-Assad
arrived here today for talks with Iranians officials on bilateral
relations and issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian president was greeted at the airport by his Iranian
counterpart Hashemi Rafsanjani, Iran's official news agency IRNA
reported.
</P>
<P>
This was Assad's second visit to Iran since the 1991 Gulf War
which changed the political map of the region.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani said that the two sides will exchange views on the
sensitive situation in the region, issues concerning Muslim and
Arab states' relations with Israel, recent developments between
Turkey and the Israeli regime and the fourth Middle East and North
Africa economic summit scheduled for later this year in Qatar.
</P>
<P>
He said Assad's visit is taking place at a time when the
U.S. Congress recognized Jerusalem as the undivided capital of the
Israeli regime and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
stated Israel's assertions of annexing the Golan Heights, a
strategic point captured by Israel in the 1967 Mideast War.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president said that Iran and Syria have had
cooperation in economic and technical fields and that the Syrian
officials accompanying Assad are expected to hold talks with their
Iranian counterparts on ways to develop mutual cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the friendly ties between Iran and Syria,
Rafsanjani said that Iranian and Syrian officials have always
consult on important regional and global issues since the triumph
of the 1979 Islamic revolution in Iran.
</P>
<P>
Assad was accompanied on the visit by Vice-President
Abdul-Halim Khaddam, Foreign Minister Farouq al-Shara and Deputy
Prime Minister in charge of Public Services Rashid Akhtarini.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
