consisting of Angola, Congo and the United Nation's High
Commissioner for Refugees for repatriating the 3000 refugees who
are willing to go back home.
</P>
<P>
The preparatory meeting for a joint defense and security
committee between Angola and Congo (B) started yesterday and
ended this morning.
</P>
<P>
Delegations headed by the interior ministers of the two
countries have arrived at Cabinda to attend the official meeting
of the Joint Defense and Security Committee over border security
issues. 
