<HEADLINE> General Motors to Establish Assembly Plant in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
J0HANNESBURG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- American car manufacturer,
General Motors, is to set up an assembly plant for its Trendy
Chevy and Cadillac vehicles in Namibia by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The company's fleet sales manager for Africa, Joe Parker, made
the announcement today in the Namibian capital, Windhoek, the
Southern African Broadcasting Association reported.
</P>
<P>
The Namibian government has already placed a large order of
Chevrolet vehicles to be assembled at a new industrial site,
south of Windhoek.
</P>
<P>
The plant, currently under construction, will initially employ
70 local workers. 
