<HEADLINE> Annan Approves New Entry Site for Humanitarian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 1 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan approved today the designation of Al-Walid at the
Iraq/Syrian border as a new entry point for the supply of
humanitarian goods to Iraq under Resolution 986 (1995), said the
Iraq Sanctions Committee.
</P>
<P>
The entry points at present are the Iraqi port of UMM Qasr,
Trebil at the Iraqi/Jordanian border and Zakho at the
Iraqi/Turkish border.
</P>
<P>
A team of United Nations independent inspection agents will be
stationed at the newly designated point to authenticate the
arrival of humanitarian supplies to Iraq in accordance with the
implementation of Resolution 986, said the committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
