<HEADLINE> Moya Clashes With Norman in Amsterdam Open Semi-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Carlos Moya of Spain and Magnus
Norman of Sweden booked their places in the semi-finals of the
Amsterdam Open tennis tournament in Amsterdam, Netherlands after
beating their respective rivals with straight-set victories on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The fourth-seeded Norman beat Christian Ruud of Norway 6-3, 7-6
after dominating the first set and resisting a second-set comeback
by Ruud to take a close tiebreak 8-6.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish player now faces top seed and world number 10 Moya
who beat compatriot Francisco Clavet 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The two Spanish showed a battle of baseliners, with Moya taking
the advantage. Moya put his opponent under pressure and move
around the court with his perfect rallies.
</P>
<P>
The second semi-final pits Marcelo Philippini of Uruguay
against Slava Dosedel of the Czech Republic. Both are unseeded.
</P>
</TEXT>
