<HEADLINE> Rapid Economic Growth Forecast for Third Quarter in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Economic growth of Shanghai,
China's largest industrial center, will continue to develop at a
fast pace in the third quarter of this year, according to a local
economic forecast.
</P>
<P>
The city's Gross Domestic Product (GDP) in the third quarter is
expected to reach 85.7 billion yuan, up 13 percent from the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The analysis, released by the Shanghai Information Center, was
based on the strong economic growth in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
In the January-June period, Shanghai's GDP rose to 154 billion
yuan, a 13.7-percent increase over last year's same period, four
percent higher than the national average.
</P>
<P>
The service trade developed rapidly, making up 44.6 percent of
its GDP. The added value of financial and insurance sectors
accounted for one third of that of the city's total service trade.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output value surged 14.4 percent to 269 billion
yuan. It has achieved a good harvest in summer grain and farm
produce.
</P>
<P>
The volume of foreign trade registered a 12.7-percent rise to
reach 7.3 billion US dollars. The export value of foreign-funded
firms increased by 40 percent, with electronic and machinery
products making up a quarter of the export.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of the year, overseas business people have
signed 888 contracts, involving a contractual value of 2.2 billion
US dollars. Some 60 percent were industrial projects. The 95 key
projects have absorbed 1.7 billion US dollars, making up three
fourths of the city's foreign funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
