<HEADLINE> Thailand to Import Raw Palm Oil to Ease Shortage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will allow fresh imports
of 20,000 tons of raw palm oil this month to ease the current
shortage of the raw material in the country's refineries.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at a meeting Thursday chaired by Deputy
Prime Minister Sukawich Rangsitphol.
</P>
<P>
The imports must be completed by August 31 on condition that
the importers have to buy some raw palm oil at a fixed price from
local farmers or extracting factories, Sukawich was quoted as
saying by local newspapers today.
</P>
<P>
Sukawich also predicted that the country's nut output is
expected to be around 2 million tons this year, 22 percent of
which will be produced in August and September.  
