<HEADLINE> First Flood Occurs On Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 1 (Xinhua) -- This year's first flood on
China's Yellow River, the country's second-largest, occured early
this morning after two days of heavy rain.
</P>
<P>
The flood peak discharge, which was recorded at the Longmen
Hydrographic Station, was 5,600 cubic meters per second at 5:18
this morning, according to a report by the Yellow River Anti-Flood
And Drought Control Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The report estimated that the flood peak discharge will
decrease to 5,000 cubic meters of water per second at Tongguan,
located further down the river, early Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
No casualties were reported and the report sounded optimistic
about the sure relief of the drought situation in North China. The
region has been suffering from higher than normal temperatures and
less rainfall this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
