<HEADLINE> Tibet To Develop Huge Copper Mine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Development of a mine containing
7.14 million tons of copper in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous
Region has been under planning.
</P>
<P>
The copper mine, with an elevation of around 5,000 meters above
sea level, is located in Changdu Prefecture in eastern
Tibet. Experts believe that opening up of the huge reserve will
help alleviate China's copper shortage. China has relied heavily
on import for copper.
</P>
<P>
Tibet plans to invest 1.2 billion yuan on some half a million
tons of copper, as its initial stage of utilizing the copper mine.
</P>
<P>
