<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Last Emperor of Vietnam Dies in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Bao Dai, the last emperor of
Vietnam who played puppet for France from 1949 to 1955, died here
today at the age of 83, Agence France-Presse reported.
</P>
<P>
Bao Dai was Vietnam's indigenous ruler from 1925 to 1945 under
the French colonial authority. He claimed independence of his country
in 1945, when Japanese troops invaded Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
In 1945, he renounced his throne after Ho Chi Minh established
a republic in Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
He was brought back to Vietnam from Hong Kong in 1949 by French
troops, who waged a ruthless war to regain France's colonial grasp
of the Asian country.
</P>
<P>
He was deposed in 1955 after the French were beat in 1954 by Ho
Chi Minh's army.
</P>
<P>
The period of puppet rule on Vietnam by Bao Dai under the
French was vividly depicted by Graham Greene in his novel "The
Quiet American." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970801.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US, Russian Astronauts Attend Chinese Children's Summer Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 1 (Xinhua) -- For the five American and Russian
astronauts who spoke at today's opening of "Science Fiction Camp"
here, fielding the whirlwind of questions from 2,000 five- and
six-year-olds was as challenging as working in a space station.
</P>
<P>
"This is no easy job," joked one of the astronauts as the kids
eagerly lined up for autographs on notebooks, envelopes, books and
caps and whatever else was handy.
</P>
<P>
"Have you ever met a spaceman?" one child asked US astronaut
Shannon Lucid, who has successfully completed a 223-day space
orbit.
</P>
<P>
Lucid, who was born in Shanghai, said no, but added she
believes there must be life on other planets.
</P>
<P>
"How did you feel the first time you flew in space?" asked
another child.
</P>
<P>
"It's like swimming in a swimming pool," Lucid said.
</P>
<P>
And then the inevitable question, "Can you see the Great Wall
from space?"
</P>
<P>
Lucid's answer, a firm no, brought a clamor of approval from
the elder members of the audience and cleared up the long-held
misperception created by local media that the Great Wall, perhaps
the most well-known symbol of Chinese culture, is the only manmade
structure that can be seen from space.
</P>
<P>
The summer camp for local schoolchildren, held in southwest
Sichuan Province, is sponsored by the publisher of the Chinese
magazine "Science Fiction World."
</P>
<P>
At today's opening ceremony, the Russian cosmonauts presented
Yang Xiao, editor-in-chief of the publication, with the Korolev
Medal on behalf of the Russian Cosmonauts Federation. The award is
the highest honor Russia usually gives to its astronauts.
</P>
<P>
Yang Chonghui, deputy secretary of the Provincial Committee of
the Communist Party of China, spoke at the event, saying that the
young people could learn from the astronauts' brave spirit and
their desire to look to the future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
