The agreement was reached during the talks between Indonesian
President Soeharto and visiting Namibian President Sam Nujome at
the Merdeka Palace here, State Secretary/Minister Moerdiono said.
</P>
<P>
Namibia has encouraged Indonesia to take advantage of the South
Africa Development Economic Cooperation (SADEC), Moerdiono said.
</P>
<P>
"SADEC provides many facilities, including easy access to the
European Union, Latin American and Namibian markets," the minister
told the press.
</P>
<P>
Nujoma, who arrived here Thursday on a five-day state visit,
told Soeharto that Namibia is inviting Indonesian businessmen to
set up joint ventures in his country, Moerdiono said.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also exchanged views on international issues
including the development of the Non-Aligned Movement (NAM) and
other issues of mutual concern, he added.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, the two countries also signed an agreement
on the formation of a commission for economic cooperation.
</P>
</TEXT>
