<HEADLINE> Council of Europe to Hold Second Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The Council of Europe (CE) will
hold its second summit in October to further promote legal,
political and cultural foundations for security.
</P>
<P>
All 40 member counties will participate in the summit meeting,
scheduled for October 10 and 11 in Strasbourg, the organization's
headquarters in France.
</P>
<P>
A declaration and an action plan on human dignity, social
cohesion, citizen security, and education in democratic values and
cultural diversity are expected to be adopted at the summit.
</P>
<P>
The first CE summit was held in Vienna in 1993, establishing
the council's role as a pan-European institution aimed at
promoting democratic security.
</P>
<P>
The CE was established in 1949 in London by 10 Western European
countries. Over the years, 30 countries have been added to the 10
founding members. The organization now includes central and
eastern European countries as well as Russia and Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
