<HEADLINE> HongkongBank Expects 5.4 Percent GDP Growth for HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The latest issue of Hong Kong
and Shanghai Banking Corp's (HKBank's) monthly economic report
said that it expects Hong Kong to achieve real gross domestic
product (GDP) growth of 5.4 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it forecast that inflation will rise by 6.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The new forecasts were updated from the bank's preliminary
forecasts of 5.2 percent GDP growth and 6.8 percent inflation made
 in December.
</P>
<P>
The bank said in 1996 Hong Kong's GDP grew 4.7 percent, while
the Consumer Price Index rose 6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The report said Hong Kong's economy performed strongly in the
first six months of this year, driven mainly by robust domestic
demand.
</P>
<P>
Buoyed by rising property and stock prices, private consumption
 expanded rapidly, while investment spending also benefited from
increased private construction activity.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, growth in Hong Kong's external trade remains
sluggish due to weak overseas demand, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
It said the strong momentum in domestic demand is expected to
continue in the second half of this year, while external trade
should improve somewhat due to stronger overseas demand.  
</P>
