not materialize ... because the nature of Zionist regime is
against peace and this regime tries to expand the areas under its
domination," Khamenei said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian leader said, "We consider expansion of ties with
Syria as an important part of our foreign policy."
</P>
<P>
"Arab countries must support Syria because it is the only
country that is bravely confronting Israel and withstanding
against pressure," he added.
</P>
<P>
In the meeting today with Iranian President-elect Mohammad
Khatami, Assad praised Iranian support for Syria and said that he
was confident that the ties between the two countries would be
boosted.
</P>
<P>
Khatami said that Iran and Syria have been two close allies
since the beginning of the Islamic Revolution in 1979.
</P>
<P>
"Undoubtedly the main common enemy of Iran and Syria is Israel
which is backed by the United States," he added.
</P>
<P>
He said "Zionist regime has consistently ignored the
inalienable rights of the Arabs and its claim to seek peace is
false."
</P>
<P>
Hafiz al-Assad arrived in Tehran for a unexpected state visit
Thursday. This is his second visit to Iran since the Iranian
Islamic revolution in 1979. He last came to Tehran in 1990.
</P>
<P>
As reports say that Tehran, Damascus and Baghdad are trying to
form a block in confrontation with the Israeli-Turkish military
alliance, Al-Assad's visit has drawn wide international attention.
