<HEADLINE> Guangxi Water Control Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The recently established Guangxi
Youjiang Water Conservancy Development Co. Ltd. will construct the
multipurpose Baise Water Control Project on the Youjiang River in
SW China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The 7.78 billion yuan project will strengthen flood control
capabilities, raise the hydropower generating capacity, enhance
shipping and irrigation, and raise the water supply.
</P>
<P>
The project will benefit over 1.87 million people living in a
73,300 ha. areas along the Youjiang River. The planned reservoir
will greatly enhance flood control capabilities and improve
irrigation on 17,700 hectares.
</P>
<P>
As part of the project, the Baise Hydropower Station will have
a 540,000 kw generating capacity and will generate some 169,000
kilowatt hours annually.
</P>
<P>
The reservoir of the project will improve shipping conditions
between Baise and the Guangxi capital of Nanning, with the massive
reservoir access to the sea via a 300 km deepwater shipping
route. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
