<HEADLINE> S. Africa to Tighten Gun Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 1 (Xinhua) -- South African Safety and
Security Minister Sydney Mufamadi has urged departments
concerned to tighten gun control to curb bloody crimes in the
country.
</P>
<P>
To control the proliferation of guns in South Africa has
become a top priority for security departments, local press today
quoted Mufamadi as saying.
</P>
<P>
Mufamadi pointed out that security departments and police
authorities would impose strict measures to fight against illegal
firearms and tighten control over licensed arms.
</P>
<P>
More than 20,000 criminals with ''serious previous
convictions'' were estimated to have legally licensed firearms,
said the minister.
</P>
<P>
A total of 195,639 firearms licences were approved last year,
in addition to a backlog of more than 25,000 applications,
according to Mufamadi. 
