<HEADLINE> India's Trade Deficit Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 1 (Xinhua) -- India's trade deficit during
the first quarter of 1997-98 fiscal year (April 1997 - March 1998)
is estimated to have gone up about 50 percent to 1,397.45 million
U.S. dollars in value terms compared with the corresponding period
last year, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Trade deficit stood at 933.4 million U.S. dollars during April
1996-June 1997 with the 49.7 percent rise largely due to a growth
in imports of 4.22 percent during the period under review.
</P>
<P>
Exports during April-June this year declined 0.95 percent to
8,134.95 million dollars as against 8,212.87 million dollars
during the first quarter of 1996-97. Imports during April-June
this year are estimated at 9,532.30 million dollars as against the
import level of 9,146.27 million dollars in the same period last
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
