<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Papers on SAR First Month Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Editorials carried in today's
local newspapers gave high marks to the performance of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) in its first month
operation.
</P>
<P>
These editorials generally held that since its establishment on
 July 1, the SAR has had a good opening characterized by social
stability, high efficiency, bullish economic sentiment and freedom
 of expression.
</P>
<P>
"This is beneficial to implementing the 'one country, two
systems' policy, to improving the economic competitiveness, to
realizing the Chief Executive's administrative policies and to
maintaining Hong Kong's stability and prosperity," Wen Wei Po said
 in its editorial.
</P>
<P>
It said that one of the characteristics of the present
conditions is that the executive and legislative bodies of the SAR
 have been coordinating very successfully, and the Chief Executive
 and the principal officials have been cooperating very well.
</P>
<P>
Another characteristic is the climbing trend of the economy, it
 added. The formerly forecast economic growth of 5.2 percent has
been readjusted to 5.4 percent. The inflation rate has been
lowered from 6.8 percent to 6.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The third characteristic is that economic relations between
Hong Kong and the mainland have become even closer, and the
handover has been deemed by overseas investors as a factor that
will lead to success in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The editorial said that the central government has empowered
the SAR Government to manage its affairs wholly on its own. This
enables Hong Kong to maintain its factors for success. The
performance of ongoing infrastructure projects, properties, land
supply and other sectors is also satisfactory.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Commercial Daily said in its editorial that the Hong
Kong Stock Market has had especially bullish performance during
the first month of the SAR, fully demonstrating investors'
confidence in Tung Chee Hwa and the SAR Government.
</P>
<P>
Ta Kung Pao said in its commentary that the first month
operation of the SAR has proven that Hong Kong people are able to
run Hong Kong and can run it better.
</P>
<P>
Many newspapers carried the results of a recent survey
conducted by the University of Hong Kong, which show that Hong
Kong people are more confident in their future and they give high
marks to the ability of the Chief Executive and the SAR
Government.  
</P>
