<HEADLINE> Decade-Long Safety Record For China's First McDonnell Douglas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 1 (Xinhua) -- On Thursday, the first plane
jointly manufactured by China and the US's McDonnell Douglas
marked a decade of safe operations.
</P>
<P>
The China Northern Airlines MD-82 has flown 24,000 hours on
more than 13,000 take-offs and landings.
</P>
<P>
It was produced by the Shanghai Aviation Industrial (Group)
Corporation and McDonnell Douglas Corp. China Northern took
delivery of it on July 31, 1987.
</P>
<P>
From 1987 to 1994, the Shanghai company has provided 35
MD-82/83s to China Eastern Airlines, China Northern, and a US
carrier.
</P>
<P>
The MD-82/83 is the largest joint project for China and the
Unites States in the aviation sector. China is now entering a key
phase in manufacturing the more sophisticated MD-90, the first of
which is scheduled for operation in April of next year, sources
say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
