<HEADLINE> China Registering Wildlife Dealers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese companies importing or
exporting wildlife and related products will have to register with
wildlife protection administrations at the provincial level by
the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of the efforts to control the wildlife import
and export business and to curb excessive trading in wildlife,
according to a circular issued by the Endangered Wild Fauna and
Flora Import and Export Administration Office recently.
</P>
<P>
Companies that fail to register by the deadline will have their
licenses suspended or revoked.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, about 200 companies have filed applications.
