<HEADLINE> HK Remains Leading Market for Luxury Watches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 1 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) is maintaining its position as the
world's leading market for luxury watches from Switzerland,
according to today's South China Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
The report said despite a drop last year, sales still exceeded
eight billion HK dollars (1.03 billion US dollars) and accounted
for 17.5 percent of all Swiss watch exports.
</P>
<P>
The local market for prestige brands kept a substantial edge
over second-placed United States, and was nearly double the sales
recorded in third-placed Japan.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC) said
 watches are by far Switzerland's biggest export, representing
nearly half of all sales to the SAR.
</P>
<P>
Watches and clocks are also Hong Kong's biggest export to
Switzerland, although the market was only worth 667 million HK
dollars (85.51 million US dollars) last year, which was less than
10 percent of Swiss exports to the SAR.
</P>
<P>
In terms of volume, Hong Kong is the world's biggest exporter
of watches, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Partly due to the interests of the watch industry, Switzerland
is also the sixth largest source of foreign industrial investment
in the SAR with 20 factories employing nearly 4,000 workers,
according to TDC sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
