<HEADLINE> Inflation Drops in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Inflation in Macao for the first
six months of the year dropped to 3.9 percent, latest statistics
show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
also show that the inflation rate reached 4.1 percent between June
 this year and June last year.
</P>
<P>
The highest level of inflation hit 8.6 percent in 1995, and has
 since declined continuously. Last year's rate was recorded at 4.8
 percent.
</P>
<P>
Compared with last May, prices of housing, transportation, food
 and drinks and clothing rose a bit in June, but prices of durable
 goods dropped a little.
</P>
<P>
Macao's main source of income relies on tourism and gambling,
which account for more than 40 percent. Other main industries
include finance, real estate and manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
The overall economy has been on a recovery since late last
year, following a two-year slowdown.  
</P>
</TEXT>
