<HEADLINE> Southeast China City Uses Hong Kong for Its Export Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Zhangzhou city of Fujian province
in southeastern China has increased co-operation with Hong Kong by
using it as a gateway for economic and trade contacts with Taiwan
and foreign countries.
</P>
<P>
By the end of April, there were 964 Hong Kong-backed
enterprises in Zhangzhou, half the overseas-funded enterprises in
the city, with 740 million U.S. dollars worth of capital.
</P>
<P>
Zhangzhou earned over 3.28 million dollars by providing labor
services for Hong Kong, which provided 22.5 percent of the 14.55
million dollars the city made from labor services.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong businessmen have also introduced a number of
Taiwanese firms to Zhangzhou, using their own success there as an
example. Most of Zhangzhou's transit trade with Taiwan went
through Hong Kong and reached 110 million dollars by the end of
last year, accounting for 62 percent of the city's total trade
volume with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Zhangzhou has four firms in Hong Kong and has
increased contacts with international markets in Southeast Asia,
America, Europe and Japan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
