Organisation (ILO) workshop concluded here Thursday with the
participants focusing their discussions on ways to improve the
African trade union leaders' capacity to respond to challenges.
</P>
<P>
In its recommendations, the workshop urged the support and
collaboration of regional and sub-regional trade unions, employer
and governmental bodies in seeking ways to respond to challenges.
</P>
<P>
The recommendations also said: " Workers should bednefit in
terms of increase in income and improvement in working conditions
and job security.''
</P>
<P>
The workshop, whose theme was ''African leadership on workers
benefits from productivity improvedment'', has attracted top African
trade union policy makers and participants from 16
engligh-speaking African countries.
</P>
