<HEADLINE> Chinese Trade Union Network in Private Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 1 (Xinhua) -- A trade union network involving
private firms is taking shape in Jiangsu Province in east China,
helping develop the private sector.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, 5,945 private firms have set up
trade unions and have provided more than 70,000 members.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu has seen a boom in the private sector. By the end of
June the number of private businesses reached 56,600. These employ
some 650,000 people and have capital assets worth 18.79 billion
yuan in total.
</P>
<P>
At present more than 35 cities and counties in the province
have trade union organizations that act on behalf of employees and
sign work contracts with private businesses, to settle problems
over hours, salaries, work benefits, medical care, and pensions.
</P>
