<HEADLINE> Assad Calls for Further Actions to Liberate Arab </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez al-Assad
called here today for further actions to liberate the occupied
Arab territories, to restore the usurped Arab rights, and to
establish just and comprehensive peace in the Mideast.
</P>
<P>
Assad made this statement in a written address to the Syrian
Armed Forces on the occasion of the Army Day on August 1, Syrian
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Assad asserted that Syria believed in just peace in the region,
but "this would not dissuade us from confronting any aggression."
</P>
<P>
The Syrian president also said, "we shall never cool down
or feel at ease so long as the Israeli occupation is in control of
certain sectors of the Arab territories. The liberation of the
occupied territory is a sacred duty which we will not hesitate to
perform and to achieve no matter what the sacrifices will be."
</P>
<P>
He added that "we have been calling for peace in our region, a
just and comprehensive peace that puts an end to aggression,
occupation and usurpation of rights. But Israel, under the rule of
the present government, has responded to our stance with further
extremism and fanaticism."
</P>
<P>
On the issue of the Golan Heights which was captured by Israel
in the 1967 Middle East war, Assad reiterated that the fate of the
Golan Heights is not to be determined by one individual or a
group, but by the legitimate owners of the land. 
</P>
