<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NE China Railway Port Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 1 (Xinhua) -- A railway port for cargo goods in
the capital of China's Heilongjiang Province opened formally today.
</P>
<P>
It will handle international container transports and is the
first Category-A inland port in the country, authorities told
Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The 37,000-sq.m. port area is designed to handle 10,000 TEU
containers annually. Another port still being built will open at
the end of 1998, on a 350,000-sq.m. area, with an annual handling
capacity of 200,000 TEUs.
</P>
<P>
Trial use of the port started in April. It has a container
transport line running to Dalian port, in neighboring Liaoning
Province.
</P>
<P>
The rail-line will also reach Suifenhe in Heilongjiang, and
Manzhouli in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region. A container
route will also be opened to Kowloon.
</P>
<P>
The move will improve Harbin's investment environment, and
narrow the gap between it and coastal areas, authorities
say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
