<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia-Pacific Ad Festival to Be Held in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Thailand will host the
Asia-Pacific Advertising Festival next year in its northern
province of Chiang Mai.
</P>
<P>
The event named "AP Adfest" is scheduled for March 4-6 next
year in Chiang Mai city, capital of Chiang Mai province, and the
festival is the first of such kind in the advertising business in
Asia, according to the steering committee of the festival, which
was formed here today.
</P>
<P>
The festival is aimed at raising awareness and standard of
advertising works and encouraging the use of the region's cultural
heritage and values in the advertising works, said the committee
which now comprises representatives from India, Indonesia, Japan,
South Korea, China, Thailand and the Asian Federation of
Advertising Associations.
</P>
<P>
Creative advertising works in television, newspapers and
magazines will also be presented for competition during the
festival.
</P>
<P>
Wu Deyu, executive vice-president of China Advertising
Association, said that China's advertising industry is very
interested in the festival.
</P>
<P>
China's fledgling ad industry hopes to exchange experiences and
ideas with its counterparts around the world, especially those in
Asia, to promote the development of the advertising business, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
