Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Patrick Weil, chief of the Research Department of the
National Center of Scientific Research and member of the Council
of Integration, Thursday submitted to Prime Minister Lionel Jospin
a report on immigration which will be subjected to parliamentary
debate in autumn. Among the 120 proposals presented in the report,
Weil suggested that the acquisition of French nationality by
children born in France of foreign parents become automatic if
they require it at the age of 18.
</P>
<P>
-- After Wednesday's bombing attack in the Mahane Jehuda
marketplace in Jerusalem, which killed 15 people and wounded 150,
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu Thursday threatened to
send troops to the Palestinian territories under the control of
the Palestinian autonomous authorities of Yasser Arafat, if
Palestinian police fail to be cooperative enough with Israel in
the search for Islamic militants.
</P>
