</P>
<P>
-- After a brief improvement of employment in May, the
unemployment rose by 0.6 percent in June in France, which now has
3,130,900 jobless people and an unemployment rate of 12.6
percent. All groups of people in terms of age and sex, except that
of women under 25 years, were affected by the newest increase of
unemployment.
</P>
<P>
-- French Defense Minister Alain Richard announced Thursday in
Bangui that France is closing the Bouar military base in the
Central African Republic and will reduce gradually the number of
soldiers in the military base of Beal in Bangui. Troubled by
endless ethnic quarrels and a series of mutinies, the Central
African Republic can no longer serve as a support point it once
was for French military actions in Africa. 
</P>
