<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined in dull
trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index fell 11.89 points to close at 1955.25 today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume shrank to 116.4 million units, valued at
299.24 million Singapore dollars (about 203.56 million U.S.
dollars). Declines led advances by 184 to 104, while 324 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Asia Food &AMP; Properties was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 11.9 million units. It was followed by
the Hong Kong Land which had 7.83 million shares traded. UIC was
next with 4.04 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
JMH 400 led the gainers of the day as it rose 20 cents to end
at 7.1 Singapore dollars. Elec and the Singapore Land gained 15
cents each to finish at 7.65 U.S. dollars and 7.4 Singapore
dollars respectively. Keppel Land closed 14 cents higher at 4.34
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Transmarco and the United Overseas Bank (UOB)
Foreign shared the top spot on the losers list as each declined 60
cents to finish at 11.3 and 15.4 Singapore dollars respectively.
NBT fell 50 cents to close at 20.5 Singapore dollars, while
Venture warrant9907 was 40 cents lower at 5.4 Singapore dollars.
</P>
