<HEADLINE> 50 Rebels Killed in North Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 1 (Xinhua) -- At Least 50 Tamil rebels were
killed and over 30 others injured in a confrontation on Thursday
with government troops in Northern province of Sri Lanka,
according to a military spokesman here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the rebels attacked the troops with
artillery and mortars and the troops retaliated, inflicting heavy
casualties on the rebels.
</P>
<P>
The rebels fled northward with their casualties. However, one
officer and 16 soldiers of the government troops were also killed
and 14 soldiers wounded in the confrontation, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war for a separate state
in the north and east of the island country since 1983.  
</P>
</TEXT>
