<HEADLINE> Grenade Attacks Kampala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- A grenade was hurled last night
in Natete police post in kampala, damaging a lorry, the local
daily the ''New Vision'' reported today.
</P>
<P>
The grenade fell between a police patrol car and a lorry whose
windsreen was damaged, the paper said, addiong that there was no
injury however.
</P>
<P>
The grenade was thrown from a Toyota brand vehicle whose
driver was arrested after the grenade attack.
</P>
<P>
This is the second grenade attack in two days in the city. On
Wednesday, thugs threw two grenades at civilians near Kibuye in
the city, in which eight people died and over 40 injured.
</P>
<P>
Security situation in the capital city has been worsening in
the recent months. Many foreign companies have been attacked in
the city by armed robbers. 
