<HEADLINE> Independent Electoral Commission to Be Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Political leaders in
Lesotho are meeting today in Maseru to select names to be
submitted to a state council for the appointment of an
independent electoral commission.
</P>
<P>
Vincent Malebo, Chairman of Leaders of the Political parties,
has given Auguest 25 as the deadline to submit the names to the
council, said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The legislation of setting up an electoral commission came
into effect at the beginning of July.
</P>
<P>
Lesotho is scheduled to hold general elections early next
year. But no exact date has been given.
</P>
<P>
However, non-governmental organisations have proposed polling
take place before March, when the current government expires its
period in office.
</P>
<P>
The southern African kingdom held its last elections in 1993,
which was won by the Basutoland Congress Party, now the country's
main opposition. 
</P>
