<DOCNO> XIE19970801.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Supports Tanzania's Road, Food Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Japan has provided 11.6
billion Tanzania Shillings (about 19 million U.S Dollars) to
improve Dar es Salaam city road and support the national food
production program, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed here on Thursday by Minister for
Finance Daniel Yona and the Japanese Ambassador to Tanzania
Shintaro Sasaki on behalf of the their respective governments.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, 6.5 billion T.Shs. (about 10.5
million Dollars) is for the
rehabilitation of roads in the city.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 8.5 million U.S. Dollars
will be used for the procurement of fertilizer and
machinery for the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
The government of Japan has been extending grant aid for the
Dar es Salaam road improvement and maintenance project since 1991
and for the agricultural sector since 1978. 
</P>
</TEXT>
