<HEADLINE> Kunming Prepares For World Garden Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Kunming, capital of southwest
China's Yunnan Province, is in the midst of an extensive
construction program as part of preparations to host the '99 World
Garden Expo.
</P>
<P>
The exposition, which will run from May-October, is expected to
attract eight to 10 million people and 30 international
organizations from 60 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The ongoing airport expansion project will raise its
annual handling capacity from two million to seven million
passengers.
</P>
<P>
Kunming, a city known for mild temperatures in all four seasons, is
also building hotels to increase its daily accomodation capacity
from 20,000 to 50,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The extensive campaign also includes road construction and
cleaning nearby Dianchi lake, one of China's major freshwater
lakes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
