<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Olympic gold medalist Tom
Dolan won the 200-meter individual medley at the U.S. Swimming
National Championships in Nashville, Tennessee on Thursday and
thus earned a place in the U.S. world championships team.
</P>
<P>
Dispite winning in two minutes and 1.18 seconds in the 200m
medley, Dolan suffered an asthma attack and complained of
dizziness and leg cramps afterwrds. He needed a brown paper bag
to aid his breathing after the race.
</P>
<P>
