mines along the Berlin Wall, causing death and injury to East
German citizens who tried to flee to the west before the two
Germanies were reunited in 1990 after four decades of separation.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, the court sentenced five military officers on
similar charges, giving them jail terms ranging from nine to 18
months. 
