elections would not be disturbed," he added.
</P>
<P>
Alatas said that he would visit Phnom Penh later this week or
earlier next month. He, along with foreign ministers of Thailand
and the Philippines, is expected to discuss political crisis there
with Second Prime Minister Hun Sen.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether Hun Sen would meet representatives of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) on Monday night,
Alatas said that the date is yet to be confirmed.
</P>
<P>
