<HEADLINE> Indonesia Plans to Buy German Submarines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia plans to buy several
submarines from Germany in the near future to beef up its warship
fleet, a senior navy officer said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A memorandum of understanding on the deal is expected to be
signed next September, Arief Kusyariadi, chief of staff of
Indonesian navy, said.
</P>
<P>
But he did not specify how many submarines would be bought or
how much the deal was worth.
</P>
<P>
However, Yusuf Effendi, director-general of The Defense
Ministry for Planning and Budget, said recently Indonesia
considered buying at least six submarines.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Bruno Hasenpusch, defense attache of the German
Embassy here, said the type of submarine to be purchased by
Indonesia was U-206.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian navy now has two U-209 submarines, also bought
from Germany, the navy chief said.
</P>
<P>
The U-206 submarine can carry 26 crew members and is smaller
than the U-209.
</P>
<P>
It is appropriate for the Indonesian navy to operate the U-206
subs, Hasenpusch said, because the U-206 subs are suitable to
control shipping lanes in the Indonesian waters, which has
thousands of islands.
</P>
<P>
Both the U-206 and U-209 are able to remain under water for
three weeks, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
