Corporation (ONGC) has shortlisted 12 foreign oil majors for a
possible alliance for deep sea exploration under the new
exploration licensing policy, ONGC sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The 12 world oil majors including Shell, Petrobras and Amereda
Hess, will be invited for technical and commercial discussions
with senior ONGC officials before their names are recommended to
the cabinet for approval.
</P>
<P>
