<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has finished the work of
laying the 64-kilometer inland section of a natural gas pipeline
running from the Yadana gas field in the Gulf of Mottma to
Thailand, the official daily The New Light of Myanmar reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The remaining part of the 350 kilometer pipeline is expected to
be completed within three months, the report said.
</P>
<P>
