<HEADLINE> Brazil Sees Increase in New AIDS Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A total of 7,552 new cases
of AIDS were registered with the Brazilian Health Ministry between
April and June this year, raising the total number of cases
registered since 1980 to 110,000.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian state with the highest number of AIDS cases is
Sao Paulo with 56,605, followed by Rio de Janeiro with 16,325, and
Minas Gerais with 7,273.
</P>
<P>
Five percent of AIDS cases registered in the last 17 years were
among the illiterate; 59 percent with only primary education, 23
percent with secondary education.
</P>
<P>
The health ministry said that it needs 200 million dollars to
supply of free medicine for 72,000 AIDS sufferers in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
