<HEADLINE> Peruvian Troops Clash With Guerrillas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Eight people, including a civilian,
were killed during two separate shoot-outs between Peruvian troops
and Shing Path guerrillas on Tuesday, military sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The clashes occurred in the central Peruvian department of
Ayacucho, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Two government soldiers and five guerrillas died during the
first battle in the Pampahuanca zone which broke out as troops
carried out routine operations.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers confiscated an AKM rifle, 20 hand grenades, 200
electoral ID carnets, explosives and subversive propaganda posters.
</P>
<P>
The other armed skirmish happened when some 20 Shining Path
guerrillas, accompanied by about 100 people, including women and
children, tried to enter the Manchete town to paint posters and
were rejected by a military patrol.
</P>
<P>
Civilian Carlos Hermilio, who was inside his vehicle when the
shooting started, died during the clash.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1980, the Shining Path is an organization of leftist
guerrillas which aims at establishing a peasant-worker's state.
</P>
</TEXT>
