<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nicaraguan Police Poorest in Central America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, JULY 31 (Xinhua) -- Nicaragua's police have the lowest
salaries of all police forces in Central America, averaging 50
U.S. dollars a month, police experts said here today.
</P>
<P>
The experts, who attended a seminar held in Managua about
crime in the region, said police officers in other isthmus
countries get salaries of between 350 and 2,000 dollars a month.
</P>
<P>
The Nicaraguan police get no social benefits and no subsidies
on food, uniforms, shoes or housing, they said.
</P>
<P>
The children of the Nicaraguan police get no subsidies
for their education and medical care.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, Honduran police officers get 70 to 75
dollars a month, the second lowest salaries for police in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Guatemalan police do better, earning 185 dollars a month, while
Costa Rica forces get 600 to 700 dollars. In Belize, police are
paid between 600 to 1,000 dollars, while their Panamanian
counterparts earn between 350 to 2,000 dollars a month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
