<HEADLINE> Tibet and Qinghai Copper Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 1 (Xinhua) -- China has recently discovered a
large copper reserve in Qamdo in southwest China's Tibet
Autonomous Region, according to the recent issue of the Science
and Technology Daily.
</P>
<P>
Preparations for the full-scale development of the precious
mineral reserve are proceeding smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The mine, called the Yulong (Jade Dragon) Copper Mine, has a
verified copper reserves of 6.5 million tons, with first-phase
development plans calling for production of 515,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The Daily also reported the discovery of a large copper reserve
in northwest China's Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
Development of the two copper mines, which are expected to
begin operations by the turn of the century, will help to meet the
nation's growing demand for the precious metal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
