<HEADLINE> Elizaveta Suvorova Claims First Gold at Modern Pentathlon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Russian Elizaveta Suvorova took the
first gold medal in the Modern Pentathlon Championships here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old Elizaveta, a college student from Mosco, had
won two titles of Modern Pentathlon champions in the junior
women's individual competitions. This time she claimed the crown
in the women's competitions.
</P>
<P>
Elizaveta wrested the women's individual gold medal with 5,240
points while Fabiana Fares from France wrapped up second with
5,083 in front of Liu Grolichova from Czech Republic 5,061.
</P>
<P>
Italy led the team standings at 14,968 points in the women's
group, followed by Russia in the second place with 14,787 and the
Czech Republic came third at 14,591.
</P>
<P>
The host team Bulgaria ranked a modest tenth with 9,372
points. 
</P>
