<DOCNO> XIE19970801.0204 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IMF Approves Three-Year Loan for Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 31 (Xinhua) --The International Monetary Fund
(IMF) today announced the approval of a three-year loan for
Mongolia under the Enhanced Structural Adjustment Facility (ESAF),
in an amount of some 45 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The loan is provided in support of the government's economic
program during 1997-2000.
</P>
<P>
The first annual loan, in an amount of 11.13 million dollars
equivalent is available in two equal semiannual installments, the
first of which can be drawn on August 6, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian government's medium-term strategy focuses on
rapidly completing the transition to a full market economy and
strengthening the foundation for strong and sustainable private
sector-led growth by reducing the size of the public sector and
fostering the development of private sector. The main objectives
of the program include to reduce inflation to single-digit rates,
achieve an annual real GDP growth rate of 6 percent and increase
official gross international reserves to the equivalent of over 15
weeks of import cover.
</P>
<P>
The ESAF is a concessional IMF facility for assisting member
countries that are undertaking economic reform programs to
strengthen their balance of payments and improve their growth
prospects. ESAF loans carry an interest rate of only 0.5 percent a
year and are repayable over 10 years, with a 5.5-year grace
period.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia joined the IMF in February 1991. Its quota is about 50
million dollars and its outstanding use of IMF financing currently
stands at about 42 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970801.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Large-Reserve Coal Mine Found In Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 1 (Xinhua) -- A coal mine which has a huge
reserve of 12 billion tons has been discovered in Shaanxi
Province, Northwest China, local industry sources reported.
</P>
<P>
This is the area's second major coalfield, located just south
of the Shenfu Coalfield, which is situated between Shaanxi and its
northern neighbor Inner Mongolia. Shenfu has a reserve of six
million tons.
</P>
<P>
An official from the province's geological bureau said that
some scientists and businessmen from Russia, South Africa, Canada
and Hong Kong have been to the mine to explore investment
opportunities.
</P>
<P>
He said that the mine, covering an area of 5,500 sq km, has
abundant river water and underground water sources. Construction
of a railway line to link the coalfield to Xi'an and Baotou, both
major cities in North China, will begin soon.  
</P>
</TEXT>
