<HEADLINE> East China Province Receives More Overseas Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 1 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
received 341,500 overseas tourists during the first half-year
period, 15.5 percent more than the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The provincial tourism bureau also said that the province
earned 137 million US dollars during this period, an increase of
29.4 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
An official of the bureau attributed the feat to the bureau's
aggressive publicity campaigns. Since the beginning of the year,
the bureau has sent four teams to the US, Canada, Japan, Malaysia,
Indonesia and some other countries to promote its tourism
highlights.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang, a mountainous coastal province, has a number of
beautiful scenic spots such as the West Lake, many Buddhist
temples, and some ancient towns built around serene rivers. The
province is also China's major tea and silk production
area.  
</P>
