<HEADLINE> Tianjin Cracks Down On Historic Relics Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, one of the major Chinese
port cities in north China, has dealt with 11 cases of smuggling
historic relics, confiscating more than 4,500 items, including
ancient coins and china, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Customs officials said that some people hide historic relics in
their exported cargo, and others conceal the goods in their
luggages.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, Tianjin Customs has handled 92 cases of smuggled
historic relics, seizing 9,791 articles.  
