<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Uses 70 Percent More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province utilized 1.2 billion US dollars of foreign investment
during the first half of the year, over 70 percent more than the
same period last year, local official sources said.
</P>
<P>
Gao Guozhu, vice governor of Liaoning Province recently
announced the statistics, saying that during this period, overseas
investors added 320 million US dollars of funding to their
projects in Liaoning, including 230 million US dollars on Dalian
Port alone.
</P>
<P>
So far, foreign investors have opened more than 2,300
representative offices in the province. Some 6,500 overseas-funded
firms are in production, with their output and export both rising
at an annual rate of 20 percent in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
He said that Liaoning will further open itself up to overseas
investors in the future, with preferential policies offered in the
petrochemical, metallurgical, machinery, electronics and
agriculture sectors.
</P>
<P>
The province also has more than 160 industrial projects waiting
for technical renovation, Gao said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
