<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 1 (Xinhua) -- All major Beijing-based
newspapers frontpaged the celebration activities to mark the 70th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Liberation Army (PLA)
Thursday and carried the full text of Jiang Zemin's speech
delivered at a grand rally held in Beijing's Great Hall of the
People on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
-- The grand rally was held yesterday by the Central Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC), the State Council and the
Central Military Commission (CMC). Over 6,000 people including top
leaders and top military officers attended the rally.
</P>
<P>
-- Jiang Zemin, the general secretary of the CPC Central
Committee, Chinese president and chairman of the CMC, delivered an
important speech.
</P>
<P>
He said that all members of the PLA must hold high unswervingly
the banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
He urged the armed forces to maintain a clear view of both
domestic and international situations, be vigilant in peace time,
strengthen their sense of responsibility and mission, and launch a
full-scale military development effort.
</P>
<P>
-- National Defense Minister Chi Haotian presided over a
reception marking the 70th anniversary of PLA's founding in the
Great Hall of the People yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Chi told the gathering that the PLA will always strictly follow
the command of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) and that of the Central Military Commission (CMC).
</P>
<P>
Chi, who is also vice-chairman of the CMC and state councillor,
said: "We will stand firm with the CPC Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at its core both in thought and action," and "We must
never lose our loyalty to the Party, to the motherland, to the
people and to socialism. We should serve the people heart and soul
and never change the nature of the people's army."
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The leading newspaper in the country carries an editorial
today to mark the 70th anniversary of the founding of PLA.
</P>
<P>
The PLA is an armed group led by the Communist Party of China
to carry out revolutionary and political duties. It is also a
strong pillar of the people's democratic dictatorship and is an
important guarantee for national security, social stability and
the unification of the motherland, it says.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 70 years, the PLA has adhered to the guidelines
and principles of the Communist Party of China and has played an
important role in founding New China, safeguarding the sacred
territories of the motherland, protecting the socialist
modernization, reform and opening drive, and promoting the
peaceful reunification of the motherland and the realization of
the smooth return of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The editorial calls on the army to adhere to Deng Xiaoping's
theory on army building and meet President Jiang Zemin's demand
that the troops "be qualified politically and competent
militarily, have a fine work style, be strictly disciplined and be
assured of adequate logistical support." 
</P>
</TEXT>
