<HEADLINE> Bank Deposits Increase in South China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 1 (Xinhua) -- Deposits of financial
institutions in south China's Guangdong province reached 997.3
billion yuan by June this year, 8.9 percent higher than the total
at the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the Guangdong branch of the People's Bank of
China show that by June 1997, the total bank savings of financial
institutions increased by 81.7 billion yuan over that of the end
of last year.
</P>
<P>
In terms of deposit structure, the total residents' and
enterprises' savings were 577.7 billion yuan and 347.5 billion
yuan, up 11 percent and 5.2 percent higher than that of the end of
1996, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that in spite of funds being diverted to housing,
medical care, education and the stock market, and also treasury
bonds issuing, deposits in Guangdong continued to increase.
</P>
