<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, Frankfurt, Paris Hit New Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Leading European stock markets
ended mixed Thursday, with London closing lower for the first time
this week while Frankfurt and Paris hitting new record closing
highs.
</P>
<P>
British shares on the London market closed near their day's
lows after a topsy-turvy day in the City, influenced by a weak
Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The Dow's overnight rise gave the FTSE 100 index early
momentum, but stocks gave up much of their gains amid more
confusion over the pound's future.
</P>
<P>
However, soft US economic figures restored confidence until the
profit takers moved in and dragged London shares down nearly 20
points to 4,907.5 by the end of the session.
</P>
<P>
German shares on the Frankfurt market, which closes before Wall
Street opens, hit another new high, boosted by the Dow's overnight
gains and the firmer dollar which is good for German exports.
</P>
<P>
The DAX-30 index closed up 17.21 points at 4,438.93 although
trading was quieter than in recent days.
</P>
<P>
The Paris bourse also ended at a new record closing high
although well off the day's peaks, supported by the settlement of
July futures and options contracts. The major CAC-40 index
finished 6.37 points up at 3,075.67.  
</P>
</TEXT>
