<HEADLINE> Ex-Im Bank, Azerbaijan Sign Project Incentive Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Export-Import Bank of the
United States (Ex-Im Bank) and Azerbaijan on Thursday signed a
project incentive agreement, which would lay the foundation for
possible financing of U.S. exports to the former Soviet republic.
</P>
<P>
Azerbaijan President Heydar Aliyev attended the ceremony at
Blair House, the President's Guest House. Signing for Azerbaijan
were Azerbaijan's finance Minister Fikret Yusifov and National
Bank Chairman Elman Rustamov, and Ex-Im Bank President and
Chairman James Harmon.
</P>
<P>
The agreement provides a framework for financing U.S. sales to
Azerbaijan where repayment is based on export revenues generated
by the borrower, rather than a sovereign guarantee of the debt by
the host country government. Repayment of loans will be
facilitated through the establishment of offshore collateral
accounts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
